<br>
Mages have good nukes, as well as &quot;free&quot; nuke items available to them.  Mages get nuke boots from Velketor, and a free nuke staff from chardok (I'm sure there are others, but there's not a reason to make a grocery list).  In fact, enchanters are the only caster class that do not have a right-clickable nuke item.  (Yes, I'm leaving out the Enchanter VP robe with the 700dmg dot over <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 7 minutes</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, because most mobs regen faster than that.)<br>
<br>
That leaves an Enchanter's damage output with 2 options. 1 - high resistant, higher taunt, bad mana-to-damage ratio nukes (the SoD proc, which tanks love for easy aggro, is a chanter nuke).  2 - charm something and buff it hoping it can out-melee a debuffed opponent.<br>
<br>
If you take away the charmed pet's damage output, you really hurt the enchanter because they have no other reliable means to increase their damage output.  They can't stick a 25+ pt damage shield on it, they cant cast a rain spell to hit the mob with a few waves, and we can't drink summoned beer &amp; cake while right clicking our shoes for unlimited manaless direct damage.  The reason charmed pets do so much damage is because it is the caster controlling them's primary damage output.  <br>
<br>
If I remember right, I could swear that a mage posted that his damage output with only pet and his Velketor nuke boots was equal to a descently equipped monk.<br>
<br>
You have to keep in mind that Verant looks at a class's overall damage output, not only 1 facet of it.  If you take away the power of charmed mobs, it is like sending you into battle with your pet, no nukes, and no right click items.<br>
<br>
Yes, in some rare situations, an enchanter can get a really good pet that can do insane damage, but keep in mind that in many of those situations, it takes finesse and a lot of luck.  The problem is that charms are not guaranteed.  If that mob is &quot;giant flagged&quot; that means he cant be mezzed.  If that charm fails, and that mob that does all that hella-nice damage output with some buddies come, that enchanter is toast.  And to those that believe that memory blur spells work everytime, you are either very mistaken or not over level 35. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/unightgod.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NightGod</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=red><B>Dranalite<B></FONT></span><br>  Posts: 191<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/5/02 7:51:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=508.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: /flame Mages</span><hr size=1> You mean my atone doesn't stick every time I cast it??<br>
